  <!-- What is Backpressure -->
  <h2 id="what-is-backpressure">What is Backpressure in Disc Centrifuges?</h2>

  <p>A paring disc pump within the disc centrifuge bowl converts the rotational momentum of the fluid into pressure. This pressure causes the liquid to discharge out of the bowl.</p>
  <p>Any restriction in the discharge passage of the liquids exerts pressure on the bowl. <strong>This externally created pressure is known as centrifuge backpressure.</strong></p>
  <p>In this article, we discuss the benefits of centrifuge backpressure, methods to create backpressure, and the disadvantages of back pressure.</p>

  <!-- Legacy hero image used as body reference image -->
